The proposed algorithm is a network simplex method, which is a popular technique for solving such problems. Hence, this paper could be classified under networks and networking.
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of combinatorial optimization problems, which is a subfield of discrete mathematics. The proposed algorithm uses combinatorial techniques to solve the budget-constrained minimum cost flow problem, which further supports this classification.
